<h1>Problem 2398 - 2009 USA TST, P6 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(N > M > 1\) be fixed integers.
  There are \(N\) people playing in a chess tournament;
  each pair of players plays each other once, with no draws.
  It turns out that for each sequence of \(M + 1\) distinct players
  \(P_0\), \(P_1\), \(\dots\), \(P_M\) such that \(P_{i-1}\) beats \(P_i\)
  for \(i=1,\dots,M\), player \(P_0\) also beat \(P_M\).
  Prove that the players can be ranked from \(1,2,\dots,N\) such that:
  whenever \(a \ge b + M-1\), player \(a\) beat player \(b\).</p>
